The paper deals with distributed algorithms for graph problems, specifically Locally Checkable Labeling (LCL) problems, which are typically studied in the context of distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves graph coloring problems, which fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory).
